CYPRESS OVERVIEW :


WebTesting / Api Testing

Modern WebApplication (Angular JS and React JS)
It uses Javascript
No relation between selenium and cypress

Open Source :

Test-runner : Free
Dashboard - paid

Node.js and come with npm module

Who can use cypress : Dev && QA
End-to -End test case
Integration tests
Unit test


Selenium vs Cypress
Selenium :
> only web
> free
> Java, python, ruby, js, c#
> chrome, ff, safari, ie, opera, edge
> runs outside of the browser
> integrate with extent and allure report

Cypress:
> web / api
> Test-runner : Free/Dashboard - paid
> js/ts
> chrome, electron, firefox
> runs inside the browser
> mocha reporter, allure

Features :
> debugging
> build in waits (automatic waits)
> video/ screenshots
> cross browser testing

Limitations
> cannot automation window application/ mobile apps
> js/ts
> limit reporting tools



Steps :

1. Download Node & NPM  https://nodejs.org/en/download
2. Create Cypress working folder
3. Generate package.json -> npm init
4. Install Cypress -> npm install Cypress
5.  Download Visual Study code editor
6. Start Cypress - npx cypress open


Running Tests/Specs

—————————————
To open cypress runner
 npx cypress open

To run all the specs under e2e folder
  npx cypress run
  npx cypress run —headed

To run single spec under e2e folder
npx cypress run  -specs "./cypress/e2e/MyFirstTest.cy.js"

Change browser
npx cypress run —browser chrome




